radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated up to 12 mm and fluid filled with several appendicoliths including a 6-mm appendicolith at the base, a 4-mm appendicolith in the mid portion and a 6-mm appendicolith near the tip. There is adjacent stranding. The lung bases demonstrate minimal dependent atelectasis and are otherwise clear. No pleural or pericardial effusion is seen. The liver, spleen, pancreas, adrenal glands, kidneys, and visualized portions of the ureters are unremarkable. The gallbladder is full, but otherwise unremarkable. The stomach and small bowel are within normal limits. Stool is seen throughout an otherwise unremarkable colon. There is no free intraperitoneal air or ascites. Visualized vasculature is unremarkable noting an accessory right renal artery. The bladder, uterus, and rectum are unremarkable. There is no free fluid in the pelvis. No concerning lytic or sclerotic osseous lesions are detected.
